. 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew" authorityName="Loew" box="[324,676,1285,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Hercostomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="caudatus">
<emphasis box="[324,581,1285,1309]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="579">Hercostomus caudatus</emphasis>
(Loew)
</taxonomicName>
, originally described in the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Loew, 1857" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1857" box="[1074,1385,1285,1310]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Gymnopternus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1074,1239,1286,1309]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="579">Gymnopternus</emphasis>
Loew, 
<number box="[1326,1385,1285,1310]" pageId="7" pageNumber="579" value="1857.0">1857</number>
</taxonomicName>
, has typical for males of 
<taxonomicName box="[393,518,1321,1345]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Sybistroma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[393,518,1321,1345]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="579">Sybistroma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shortened antennal pedicel and tripartite arrangement of basiventral lobes and hypandrium in addition to elongate setulose apicoventral epandrial lobes. Therefore, a new combination for the species is here proposed.
</paragraph>
